Date of Birth: February 19, 1793<br/>
Birthplace: Saint Clair Township, Pennsylvania, USA<br/>
Excommunicated: September 8, 1844<br/>
Death: July 14, 1876<br/>
<br/>
Born Feb. 19, 1793, at Saint Clair Township, Allegheny Co., Pennsylvania, , to William Rigdon and Nancy Bryant.
Ordained high priest in June 1831 by Lyman Wight;
set apart as a counselor to President Joseph Smith on March 8, 1832, sustained as first counselor on March 18, 1833, at age 40;
excommunicated Sept. 8, 1844; died July 14, 1876, at Friendship, Allegany Co., New York, at age 83.